ProtoResult:
. "Suppose that \begin{equation} |f(x)|\le M,\quad a\le x\le 
   b, \end{equation} and let $P'$ be a partition of $[a,b]$ 
   obtained by adding $r$ points to a partition $P=\{x_0,x_1, 
   \dots,x_n\}$ of $[a,b]$ Then \begin{eqnarray} S(P)\ge S(P') 
   \ge S(P)-2Mr\|P\| \\ and \\ s(P)\le s(P') \le s(P)+2Mr\|P\| 
   . \end{eqnarray}"
